<recipe>
<title>
Coconut Lime Sugar Cookie Bars
</title>
<details>
PREP TIME: 20 minutes
COOK TIME: 20 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 40 minutes
SERVINGS: 48 bars
</details>
<ingredients>
SUGAR COOKIES
3 cups all-purpose flour
1 tablespoon cornstarch
1 teaspoon baking powder
1/2 teaspoon kosher salt
1/4 teaspoon baking soda
1 cup butter , at cool room temperature
1 1/4 cups granulated sugar
1 large egg
2 tablespoons sour cream
2 teaspoons vanilla extract
1/2 teaspoon almond extract
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 350 F. Line a 9x13-inch baking dish with foil, leaving an overhang at both ends. Grease foil with nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.
In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, cornstarch, baking powder, salt, and baking soda. Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat butter on high for 30 seconds. 
Scrape down bowl, and beat in sugar until well-combined. 
Add egg, and beat until combined. 
Stir in sour cream, vanilla extract, and almond extract. 
Spread dough into prepared baking pan.
Bake 20-25 minutes, or until light golden brown at the edges. 
Remove from oven, and let bars cool in pan to room temperature.
To make the frosting, beat butter on high for 30 seconds in a large bowl.
Mix in remaining ingredients, and stir together until well-combined.
Spread frosting over cooled bars. 
Top with toasted coconut chips and additional lime zest, if desired. 
Cover, and store frosted bars in the fridge. 
</instructions>
</recipe>
